---
description: Structural layout enforcement and geometry stabilization.
glob: ["**/*.tsx", "**/*.jsx", "**/*.html", "**/*.vue"]
alwaysApply: true
---

# FLAGSHIP DESIGN PROTOCOL

Build layout structure from approved design plan.

Do not reinterpret intent.

---

# STRUCTURE ENFORCEMENT

If layout direction = horizontal:

- Use explicit grid or flex row.
- Two visible columns required.
- Prevent full-width stacking on desktop.
- Lock column widths using grid-template-columns.
- Do not rely on content sizing.

If ratio defined:

- Use explicit structural ratio.
- Do not approximate.

If height = full viewport:

- Use min-height: 100vh.
- Never simulate with padding.

---

# CONTAINER RULES

- Lock max-width (1200–1320px unless otherwise specified).
- Center container.
- Maintain structural symmetry unless asymmetry intentional.

---

# RESPONSIVE RULES

If mobile behavior defined:

- Explicitly implement breakpoint logic.
- Collapse to single column when required.
- Preserve hard constraint ordering.

Never guess mobile behavior.

---

# STRUCTURAL STABILITY RULE

Never:

- Use overflow hacks
- Fake ratios
- Allow content to define column width
- Modify direction decided upstream

If structure violates hard constraints:
Regenerate before output.